        <header>
            <h1><i class="fas fa-plane"></i> 737 VR Speed Calculator</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Enter wind speed and flap setting to get VR speeds for different 737 models</p>
        </header>
        
        <div class="instructions">
            <p><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>How to use this calculator:</strong></p>
            <ol style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Enter wind speed in knots (positive for headwind, negative for tailwind)</li>
                <li>Select flap setting from the dropdown menu (default is 5°)</li>
                <li>Click "Calculate VR Speed" or simply change any input value</li>
                <li>Read the calculated VR (rotation) speeds for each 737 model</li>
            </ol>
            <p style="margin-top: 10px;"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> <strong>Note:</strong> This calculator assumes maximum takeoff weight (MTOW) conditions. Results are for reference only. Always consult official flight manuals for actual flight operations.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="input-section">
            <div class="input-group">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-wind"></i> Environmental Conditions</h2>
                
                <div class="input-row">
                    <label for="wind">Wind Speed (knots)</label>
                    <input type="number" id="wind" value="10" min="-50" max="50" step="1">
                    <div class="wind-info">
                        <span>Positive = Headwind</span>
                        <span>Negative = Tailwind</span>
                        <span>0 = No wind</span>
                    </div>
